# Book Cover Image on Home Page

## Context

The book home/landing page (`renderBookPage()` in `client.tsx`) currently shows title, author, description, and chapter list — but no cover image. The `Book` type already has a `coverPath` field and the Vite plugin auto-detects `cover.jpg`/`cover.png`, but SVG isn't supported and the cover is never rendered. Both examples (`flatland`, `frankenstein`) have `cover.svg` files and set `cover: cover.svg` in `_book.yaml`.

## Files to Modify

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `packages/pressy/src/vite/plugin.ts` | Fix cover discovery (add SVG), serve cover in dev, emit in build |
| `packages/pressy/src/runtime/client.tsx` | Render cover image in `renderBookPage()`, add cover CSS |

## Implementation

### Step 1: Fix cover discovery in plugin.ts (~line 95)

Update `discoverBooks()` to support SVG and honor `metadata.cover` from `_book.yaml`:

```ts
// Use metadata.cover if specified, otherwise auto-detect
const coverFile = metadata.cover && existsSync(join(bookPath, metadata.cover))
  ? metadata.cover
  : existsSync(join(bookPath, 'cover.jpg')) ? 'cover.jpg'
  : existsSync(join(bookPath, 'cover.png')) ? 'cover.png'
  : existsSync(join(bookPath, 'cover.svg')) ? 'cover.svg'
  : undefined
const coverPath = coverFile ? join(bookPath, coverFile) : undefined
```

Also ensure `metadata.cover` is always set when a cover is found (so the client knows the filename):
```ts
if (coverFile) metadata.cover = coverFile
```

### Step 2: Serve cover files in dev middleware (plugin.ts ~line 530)

In the `configureServer` middleware, before the route matching, intercept cover file requests:

```ts
// Serve book cover images from content directory
if (pathname.match(/^\/books\/[^/]+\/cover\./)) {
  const parts = pathname.split('/')
  const bookSlug = parts[2]
  const book = manifest.books.find(b => b.slug === bookSlug)
  if (book?.coverPath && existsSync(book.coverPath)) {
    // serve the file with appropriate content-type
  }
}
```

### Step 3: Emit cover files in build (plugin.ts `generateBundle`)

In the `pressy:build` plugin's `generateBundle()`, emit each book's cover as a static asset:

```ts
for (const book of manifest.books) {
  if (book.coverPath && existsSync(book.coverPath)) {
    const ext = book.coverPath.split('.').pop()
    const fileName = `books/${book.slug}/cover.${ext}`
    this.emitFile({ type: 'asset', fileName, source: readFileSync(book.coverPath) })
  }
}
```

### Step 4: Render cover in `renderBookPage()` (client.tsx ~line 159)

Add a centered hero cover image above the existing header:

```jsx
<div class="pressy-home">
  {book.metadata.cover && (
    <div class="pressy-cover">
      <img
        src={`${basePath}/books/${book.slug}/${book.metadata.cover}`}
        alt={`${book.metadata.title} cover`}
        class="pressy-cover-img"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>
  )}
  <header class="pressy-home-header">
    ...existing title/author/description...
  </header>
```

### Step 5: Add cover CSS to `HOME_STYLES` (client.tsx ~line 486)

Centered hero layout with book-like shadow:

```css
.pressy-cover {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 2rem 1rem 1rem;
}

.pressy-cover-img {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 360px;
  height: auto;
  aspect-ratio: 5 / 8;
  object-fit: cover;
  border-radius: 4px;
  box-shadow:
    0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1),
    0 12px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
}

@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .pressy-cover-img {
    max-width: 240px;
  }
}
```

## Verification

1. `pnpm -r --filter './packages/**' build` — no errors
2. `pnpm dev:flatland` — cover.svg renders on home page in dev mode
3. `pnpm build:flatland` — cover.svg appears in `dist/books/flatland/cover.svg`
4. Cover is centered, has shadow, scales responsively
5. Themes work — cover looks good on light, dark, and sepia
